+#### Operator interpretation — `trading_slo_tick_to_trade_violation` (TRD-089)
+
+Tick-to-trade is measured on the **live hot path** in `StrategyRunner.run_scan_cycle`:
+
+| Stamp | Event | Source |
+|-------|-------|--------|
+| **T₀** | OFI scan trigger for the symbol (just before `generate_signal`) | `strategy_runner.py` |
+| **T₁** | Gateway HTTP submit dispatch | `execution_actor.execute()` → `_gateway_dispatch` |
+| **T₂** | Broker acknowledgement (non-rejected `OrderResponse`) | `execute()` returns `client_order_id` |
+
+`latency_ms = (T₂ − T₀) × 1000` → `record_tick_to_trade()` → `trading_tick_to_trade_ms` (gauge) and `trading_tick_to_trade_ms_hist_*` (histogram). Each routed decision also carries `tick_to_trade_ms` in its `ROUTED` JSONL audit row (audit remains source of truth).
+
+| Reading | Meaning | Operator action |
+|---------|---------|-----------------|
+| `trading_tick_to_trade_ms_hist_count == 0` | No live/paper order has routed yet (e.g. pure shadow soak) | Expected on `:9108`; no action. SLO gauge stays `0`. |
+| gauge `= 1`, low sample (`hist_count < 100`) | p99 estimate from a thin histogram | Treat as **advisory**; do not gate promotion on it until sample is meaningful. |
+| gauge `= 1`, healthy sample | Estimated **p99 > 10 ms** SLO breach on the execution path | Investigate broker/network latency before scaling caps; **do not** promote phase. |
+| gauge `= 0`, healthy sample | p99 within SLO | Latency-clean; safe input to the promotion scorecard. |
+
+**Shadow invariant:** on `:9108` (`TRADING_DEPLOYMENT_PHASE=shadow`) `trading_tick_to_trade_ms_hist_count` must remain **0** — a non-zero value during shadow indicates an unexpected live submit and should be treated as an incident.
