+# Prop Desk Strategy — Direction & Trajectory
+
+**Scope:** The unifying thesis behind `hibs-bet` (football), `hibs-racing` (racing), and `trading_core` / Harvested Execution (US equities). This document records *direction*; it does not change any gate. Operational GO/NO-GO lives in [MASTER_OPERATIONS_SCORECARD.md](./MASTER_OPERATIONS_SCORECARD.md).
+
+---
+
+## 1. The thesis — a private, automated, multi-strategy prop desk
+
+This is **not** a retail SaaS to sell, nor a tipping bot. It is a **private proprietary trading desk** where the code is the asset that converts market data into capital. **You eat what you kill.**
+
+The products are not separate businesses — they are **strategy lanes on a single trajectory**, deliberately sequenced so we bank capital with the cheapest, highest-margin strategy before spending infrastructure budget on faster, harder ones.
+
+```
+Stage 1: Line-Shopper (+EV)  →  Stage 2: Statistical Arbitrage  →  Stage 3: Market-Making (HFT liquidity)
+        [bank capital]                 [scale the edge]                  [Redis-level infra]
+        NOW                            NEXT                              LATER
+```
+
+| Principle | Implication |
+|-----------|-------------|
+| Eat what you kill | Every lane must produce **audited, realized** edge before capital scales. |
+| Highest margin first | Line-shopping / +EV has the lowest barrier and best margin → it banks the starting capital. |
+| Infra follows proof | Arb and market-making are only funded once Stage 1 P&L justifies the data/latency spend. |
+| Audit is non-negotiable | Risk → Execution → Reconciliation boundaries and closed-loop audit apply to **every** lane (institutional-grade++). |
+
+---
+
+## 2. Stage 1 — Line-Shopper / +EV (NOW: banking starting capital)
+
+Find prices that are mispriced vs a calibrated model and take the best available line. Highest margin, lowest barrier; this is where almost all *built* value currently sits.
+
+| Asset | Role | State | Primary gate / blocker |
+|-------|------|-------|------------------------|
+| **Football** (`hibs-bet`) | +EV vs bookmaker 1X2 lines (line-shopped best price) | Engineering **A−**; evidence **C** | Forward odds/CLV must accumulate (7d ≥50% capture, CLV n≥25) before stake scale. Launch **2026-06-11**. |
+| **Racing** (`hibs-racing`) | LightGBM place-ranking + paper value picks | Built; daily lane **not green** | NA ingest bug in `daily-refresh-cards`; Matchbook coverage ~13%. Formal gate **2026-06-19**. |
+| **+EV equities** (`trading_core`, OFI) | Microstructure +EV via order-flow imbalance | Most engineered; **shadow, zero submits** | Day-15 verdict **2026-06-18** needs `SHADOW_WOULD_ROUTE` + acceptable slippage. |
+
+**Stage-1 reality:** plumbing is strong everywhere; the missing ingredient is **realized, audited edge on forward data** — i.e. actual banked P&L. No lane has taken live capital yet. *That is the whole point of Stage 1.*
+
+**Exit criteria → Stage 2:** at least one lane clears its evidence gate and books real, reconciled P&L sufficient to fund Stage-2 infrastructure.
+
+---
+
+## 3. Stage 2 — Statistical Arbitrage (NEXT: scaling the edge)
+
+Exploit *relative* mispricings (cross-book, cross-market, pairs/baskets) rather than single-line absolute edge.
+
+**Status: greenfield — effectively 0% built.**
+
+| Reusable today | New work required |
+|----------------|-------------------|
+| Reconciliation engine, WAL ledger, risk kernel | Dedicated arb/stat-arb strategy module (cross-book dutching, pairs, mispricing detection) |
+| Multi-book odds capture (raw material for cross-book arb) | Simultaneous **multi-venue execution** (today: single-broker Alpaca; betting side has no automated placement — affiliate links only) |
+| Promotion-scorecard / evidence-pack pattern | Tight latency budgeting so both legs fill before prices move |
+
+**Dependency:** only sensible to start once Stage 1 banks capital and the trading promotion path clears micro. Reuse the existing Risk → Execution → Reconciliation perimeter; do not fork a second execution stack.
+
+---
+
+## 4. Stage 3 — Market-Making / HFT liquidity provision (LATER: infra leap)
+
+Provide two-sided liquidity and earn the spread. Highest ceiling, highest infrastructure barrier.
+
+**Status: aspirational — infrastructure not in place.**
+
+| Already leaning this way | Hard gaps |
+|--------------------------|-----------|
+| `trading_core` is microstructure-aware (OFI, dual-lane, WSS market data) | **Redis-level (in-memory) hot path** — today the stack is SQLite-WAL / "zero-dependency": ideal for *audit integrity*, wrong tool for *quote-update latency* |
+| p99 tick-to-trade **< 10 ms** SLO already defined (`metrics.py`) | Two-sided quoting + inventory-risk management (none today) |
+| **TRD-089** tick-to-trade telemetry now wired on the live path | Low-latency / co-located market data; production latency *measurement* before optimization |
+
+**First concrete step (done):** [TRD-089](./TRD-089-LATENCY.md) — you cannot make markets if you cannot yet *measure* tick-to-trade in production. The wiring landed; live verification is gated to 2026-06-18.
+
+---
+
+## 5. Consolidated roadmap
+
+| Stage | Strategy | Asset(s) | Built? | Real blocker |
+|-------|----------|----------|--------|--------------|
+| **1 — now** | Line-shop / +EV | football, racing, OFI equities | Infra ✅ / edge ❌ | Bank audited forward edge |
+| **2 — next** | Statistical arbitrage | new module (reuse recon/ledger) | ~0% | Stage-1 capital; multi-venue execution |
+| **3 — later** | Market-making / HFT | `trading_core` evolution | microstructure seeds only | Redis hot path; TRD-089 measurement first |
+
+**Sequencing rule:** do not start Stage *N+1* engineering spend until Stage *N* has produced reconciled, banked P&L. Football WC launch (11 Jun), trading Day-15 (18 Jun), and racing gate (19 Jun) are the near-term Stage-1 checkpoints.
+
+---
+
