+## Hand-off: `EvidenceVerdict` payload contract
+
+Both lanes collapse to one schema; downstream reads `grade`/`promotable`/`n` and is agnostic to how significance was extracted. Exposed at `GET /api/health` → `audit_ops.evidence` (value legs) and `audit_ops.clv_beat_close` (CLV), plus `audit_ops.evidence_as_of` / `evidence_source` provenance.
+
+```jsonc
+{
+  "metric": "roi" | "proportion",   // discriminator: how to read the CI fields
+  "grade": "empty" | "insufficient" | "thin" | "sufficient",
+  "promotable": false,              // true only when grade == "sufficient"
+  "n": 0,                            // sample size (legs / CLV rows)
+  "roi_pct": null,                   // point estimate (ROI% or beat-rate%); null when n==0
+  "roi_ci_low_pct": null,            // CI lower bound (bootstrap ROI / Wilson rate); null when n==0
+  "roi_ci_high_pct": null,           // CI upper bound; null when n==0
+  "significant_positive": false,     // CI lower bound clears the null (0 for ROI, 50% for rate)
+  "beats_baseline": null,            // vs baseline (null if none supplied)
+  "reason": "…",                     // human-readable verdict rationale (audit/UI verbatim)
+  // lane-specific self-documenting hurdle:
+  "min_edge_magnitude_pct": 0.0,     // value lane (HIBS_VALUE_MIN_EDGE_PCT)
+  "min_clv_pp": 0.0                  // CLV lane (HIBS_CLV_MIN_PP)
+}
+```
+
+Producers: `evidence_stats.classify_evidence` (roi), `classify_binomial_evidence` / `classify_clv_edge` (proportion). Empty-state safe (`n==0` → CI fields `null`, `promotable=false`).
+
+### Env staging for promotion floors (deploy pipeline)
+| Var | Default | Stage as | Notes |
+|-----|---------|----------|-------|
+| `HIBS_VALUE_MIN_EDGE_PCT` | `0.0` | **0.0 (inert)** | Raise only on a sweep recommendation (weighted F-β) once forward legs exist. Zero-regression default = significance-only. |
+| `HIBS_CLV_MIN_PP` | `0.0` | **0.0 (inert)** | Same: tune from `evidence_sweep` after CLV rows land. Do not raise during a gate freeze. |
+
+Both are read at request time (`os.getenv`), so changing them is a config-only redeploy — no code change. They affect *grading/promotion only*, never the prediction engine, DQ, or stored snapshots.
+
