+# Racing Gate-Coverage — Institutional++ Amendments (hibs-racing hand-off)
+
+Five amendments to the gate-coverage precheck so `retest_ready` is a **cohort-aware,
+provenance-stamped, significance-tested** verdict — not a single flat density threshold
+that an unfillable denominator (maidens) can never clear.
+
+**Reference implementation (drop-in, tested):** [`handoff/racing_gate_reference.py`](../handoff/racing_gate_reference.py)
+— pure stdlib, deterministic, zero cross-repo deps; the Wilson interval is inlined
+verbatim from the already-unit-tested `evidence_stats`. Tests: `handoff/test_racing_gate_reference.py` (8 passing). Lift the functions into `hibs-racing` (or vendor the file).
+
+> Cannot be committed to `hibs-racing` from the football-app cloud agent (separate
+> local-only repo). This is the executable hand-off; apply it in the racing repo.
+
+---
+
+## 1. Maiden-stratified addressable cohort (the key fix)
+Pilot density 56.5% = ~70% `official_rating` (maidens have **no prior OR by race design**) × ~78% RTF. A flat 85% floor over a cohort containing maidens is **unachievable by construction** — you can enrich RTF to 100% and still FAIL.
+
+- `classify_race_cohort(card)` → `addressable` | `maiden`.
+- Floors are per-cohort (`DEFAULT_COHORT_FLOORS = {addressable: 85%, maiden: 60%}`), and **only `addressable` is blocking** (`BLOCKING_COHORTS`). Maidens are reported against an advisory floor and never block `retest_ready`.
+- `gate_coverage_by_cohort(...)` returns per-cohort verdicts; `retest_ready` = every blocking cohort clears its floor.
+
+## 2. Composite config hash (stable) + data fingerprint (changes)
+Your step-3 re-audit pins `--snapshot-config-hash fb9402`. **Confirm its semantics:**
+
+- `gate_config_hash(gate_config_version, manifest)` — hashes **config + column manifest only**, never row data → **stable across re-enrich**. Use this for `--snapshot-config-hash`; re-stamp → re-audit stays anchored.
+- `data_content_fingerprint(row_count, covered_count, window…)` — **changes** when enrich/re-stamp alters coverage. The runbook should **assert the fingerprint moved** after recovery (proof the re-stamp landed) while the config hash stays constant.
+
+If `fb9402` is currently a *content* hash, step 3 must use the **post-re-stamp** value; if it's a config-version hash, reusing it is correct. Make it explicit either way.
+
+## 3. Versioned gate-critical column manifest + dual-definition density
+Narrowing the audit to gate-critical columns is correct (kills false 0% from sparse optional fields like `form_trip_change_f`) — but it must not silently move goalposts.
+
+- `GateColumnManifest(version, runner_columns, snapshot_columns)` — **reviewed, versioned**, with `manifest_hash()` stamped into every audit output.
+- `dual_definition_density(...)` reports density under **both** the gate-critical set **and** the full set, so the gap is attributable (sparse optional vs genuinely missing gate inputs). Bump `version` on any column change; it propagates into the config hash (#2).
+
+## 4. Enrich-recovery guards (before the long batch)
+`enrich_recovery_precheck(quota_remaining, quota_needed_estimate, checkpoint_date, window_end, milestone_days)`:
+- **Quota headroom** with a +20% safety margin (don't stall mid-window on RP limits).
+- **Checkpoint-behind-window** sanity (there is something to recover).
+- **Milestone re-audit cadence** (default every 30 enriched days) — re-audit *incrementally* to catch a re-stalled checkpoint or enrich drift early, not after a multi-hour run.
+
+Run under `caffeinate`; keep the checkpoint idempotent (you already resume from Nov 19); have a kill switch.
+
+## 5. Uniform verdict for the cross-lane scorecard
+`racing_gate_verdict(audits, …)` collapses per-(lane, source) cohort audits into one block matching the betting/trading `EvidenceVerdict` contract (`metric`, `promotable` = `retest_ready`, `as_of`, `config_hash`, `reason`). `coverage_verdict` grades on the **Wilson lower bound ≥ floor** (not the point estimate), so the gate never passes on coverage that is within noise of the floor — identical rigor to the CLV beat-close gate. Emit it into the [Master Operations Scorecard](./MASTER_OPERATIONS_SCORECARD.md) so racing GO/NO-GO sits beside football and trading.
+
+---
+
+## Corrected re-test runbook
+```bash
+# 1. Resume enrich (long-running — checkpoint Nov 19). Pre-flight the guards first.
+caffeinate -ims hibs-racing batch-enrich-recovery        # re-audit at each ~30-day milestone
+
+# 2. Re-stamp snapshots once full-window enrich clears the ADDRESSABLE floor (not maidens)
+hibs-racing snapshot-backfill --start 2025-11-01 --end 2026-05-22 --force
+
+# 3. Re-audit BOTH sources, cohort-stratified. Use the STABLE config hash; assert the
+#    data fingerprint changed vs the pre-recovery run.
+hibs-racing gate-coverage-audit --start 2025-11-01 --end 2026-05-22 \
+  --lanes gate3,gate5,gate7 --source both \
+  --cohort-stratified --blocking-cohort addressable \
+  --snapshot-config-hash "$(hibs-racing gate-config-hash)"   # stable config hash, not fb9402 literal
+
+# Promote only when racing_gate_verdict.retest_ready == true on BOTH sources.
+# Do NOT run gate-impact --walkforward before then.
+```
+
